  <div class="ct">
  
<p>I'm at a refugee conference in Florida today, hanging out with a whole mess of Cubans. &nbsp;A lot of them, especially the younger ones, get it. &nbsp;But some of these older conservative Cubans are really a mess, in terms of any sort of consistency or logic. &nbsp;They sure don't much care for their poorer, darker brothers from Mexico and Central America, do they? &nbsp;</p>
<p>I don't really have a problem with rather lax immigration rules for Cubans, and I can't help but like Cubans generally despite disliking their politics so much. But they have a special deal, and it's not exactly fair to everyone else. Makes it especially sad when they want to restrict entry for others. &nbsp;And my God, if there was any population from some benighted island in the Caribbean that needs a break, it's the Haitians! &nbsp;Just compare how the US treats Cubans compared to Haitians! &nbsp;I oppose guest worker programs that don't lead to citizenship, but I could see making an exception to allow more Haitians to earn money in the US and repatriate it... there's no way that island survives without remitted income.</p>

  </div>
